      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nausea and tremors are common side effects of lithium, especially when you first start taking it, so this is likely just your body adjusting. You should keep taking your medication exactly as prescribed, but you must contact your doctor immediately if the shaking gets worse or if you experience vomiting, confusion, or severe diarrhea. Do not stop taking the lithium on your own, as sudden withdrawal can be dangerous, and your doctor may adjust your dose or give you extra water to help your body clear the medication safely.",
