      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Increasing your water intake is a good idea, but you should not drink \"way more\" than usual because it can actually lead to dangerous dehydration or electrolyte imbalances. You should drink water steadily throughout the day, but if your headaches persist or worsen, you need to call your doctor immediately to check your lithium levels. Do not try to self-adjust your dosage or take extra fluids as a cure-all, as this could mask serious symptoms that require professional medical intervention.",
